&lt;h2&gt;Information for Instructors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Freshmen&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;There will be an instructor meeting 30 minutes before Slot 1 on Day 1.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;There is no thuggishness allowed on the ditch.  You will be a happy, polite instructors.  Many of the students have traveled long distances and paid several, sometimes dozens of dollars to see you.  We do not need splash damage because your special friend got you riled up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Repeat Offenders&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;No, the next SKBC will not be at a Casino.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If you have a free instruction slot, consider looking for classes that need assistance.  Specifically, team classes, or classes which either many students (more than 20) or too few students (less than 5).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If you notice that there are many students who seem to be out of their depth in an advanced or one-on-one class, it may help to pull these students aside and go over the material from a more fundamental perspective.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
